Package org.efs.activator

Enum Class EfsAgentState

java.lang.Object
java.lang.Enum<EfsAgentState>
org.efs.activator.EfsAgentState
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable, Comparable<EfsAgentState>, Constable
public enum EfsAgentState extends Enum<EfsAgentState>
Lists the possible efs agent states. These states include:
  1. STOPPED: Agent is fully stopped and ready to be either started or the application halted.
  2. STARTING: Agent is transitioning from STOPPED to STAND_BY.
  3. STAND_BY: Agent is successfully started and ready to be activated or stopped.
  4. ACTIVATING: Agent is transitioning from STAND_BY to ACTIVE.
  5. ACTIVE: Agent is successfully started and active meaning the agent is fully operational. It may now be either deactivated or stopped.
  6. DEACTIVATING: Agent is transitioning from ACTIVE to STAND_BY.
  7. STOPPING: Agent is transitioning from STAND_BY to STOPPED.

These agents states ordering is significant. Activation advances from STOPPED to STAND_BY and ends at ACTIVE. De-activation is in the opposite order.

Author:
Charles W. Rapp

      public static final EfsAgentState STOPPED

      This is a transition state.

    • STAND_BY

      public static final EfsAgentState STAND_BY
      Agent is successfully started but not yet active. The agent may be either activated or stopped at this point.

      This is a persistent state.

    • ACTIVATING

      Agent is in this temporary state while transitioning from STAND_BY to ACTIVE. If activation fails, then agent returns to STAND_BY state.

      This is a transition state.

    • ACTIVE

      public static final EfsAgentState ACTIVE
      Agent is both successfully started and active. This means the agent is fully up. Agent may either be deactivated or fully stopped at this point.

      This is a persistent state.

    • DEACTIVATING

      public static final EfsAgentState DEACTIVATING
      Agent is in this temporary state while transitioning from ACTIVE to STAND_BY. If the deactivation fails, then agent still moves to STAND_BY state.

      This is a transition state.

    • STOPPING

      public static final EfsAgentState STOPPING
      Agent is in this temporary state while transitioning from STAND_BY to STOPPED. If the stop fails, then agent still moves to the STOPPED state.

      This is a transition state.
